'''José Raúl Rangel Aguilar''' (born 25 February 2000), commonly known as "'''Tala Rangel'''", is a Mexican professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[C.D. Guadalajara|Guadalajara]] and the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

==Club career==
Rangel began his professional career at [[C.D. Guadalajara|Guadalajara]], rising through the club's youth academy before making his senior debut for affiliate side [[C.D. Tapatío|Tapatío]] on 20 September 2020 in a 3–0 victory over Alebrijes de Oaxaca.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://el.soccerway.com/matches/2020/09/21/mexico/liga-de-ascenso/tapatio/zacatepec/3335671/ |title=Tapatío vs. Alebrijes de Oaxaca - 20 September 2020|publisher=Soccerway|access-date=1 April 2024}}</ref> He went on to make his first-team debut for Guadalajara on 1 October 2023, in a match that ended in a 1–1 draw against Toluca.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chivasdecorazon.com.mx/es/noticias/36876/10-cosas-que-no-sabas-del-Tala-Rangel |title=10 cosas que no sabías del 'Tala' Rangel|publisher=Club Deportivo Guadalajara|access-date=1 April 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Rangel made his debut for the senior [[Mexico national football team|national team]] on 5 June 2024, in a friendly against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] at the [[Empower Field at Mile High]] in Denver, he played the full game as Uruguay won 4–0.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/692532|title=Mexico v Uruguay game report|date=5 June 2024}}</ref>

